How to use functor

functor is pointer of function
we can use it as follows
void my_functor_function(int x, int y)
{
  sum = x + y;
}
main()
{
  void (*functor)(int)(int) = &my_functor_function;
  functor(10, 20);
}

why we have to use it because it is easy to handle more informational parameters that we need
for example,
class wow
{
public:
  wow(){};
  wow~(){};
  int operator + (int x, int y) const{
  return sum = x + y;
  }
};
int main()
{
  my_fuction(x,wow(y)); // here wow operator calls on object of wow
}
